and%20chemistry%20with%20the%20interviewer%20could%20all%20be%20clues.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20transcribed%20conversation%20with%20Michael%20Doolin%2C%20CEO%20of%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cloverhr.co.uk%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EClover%20HR%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20and%20former%20human%20resources%20director%20at%20PwC%2C%20British%20Airways%2C%20and%20DPD%20in%20Ireland.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20very%20common%20for%20job%20candidates%20to%20be%20uncertain%20about%20how%20a%20job%20interview%20has%20gone.%20People%20get%20nervous%20and%20unsure%20during%20interviews%20%E2%80%94%20and%20body%20language%20is%20not%20easy%20to%20read%20when%20meeting%20someone%20for%20the%20first%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPreparing%20is%20the%20best%20way%20to%20mitigate%20the%20risk%20of%20an%20interview%20going%20poorly.%20Before%20entering%20the%20room%2C%20ensure%20you're%20confident%20in%20your%20preparation%20and%20yourself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20come%20out%2C%20ask%20yourself%3A%20Could%20I%20have%20done%20any%20better%3F%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20can%20answer%20%26quot%3Byes%26quot%3B%20to%20that%20question%2C%20your%20success%20landing%20the%20role%20will%20depend%20on%20your%20credibility%20and%20whether%20the%20interviewers%20relate%20to%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can't%20always%20trust%20your%20gut%20feeling%20on%20whether%20it%20went%20well.%20In%20my%20experience%2C%20I'd%20say%20it's%20right%2050%25%20of%20the%20time.%20Alongside%20your%20gut%20reaction%2C%20here%20are%20seven%20signs%20that%20an%20interview%20was%20successful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bf9fd866-a502-4f72-8986-676e4dca75a3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20received%20a%20job%20offer%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ultimate%20sign%20that%20an%20interview%20went%20well%20%E2%80%94%20and%20this%20is%20very%20rare%20%E2%80%94%20is%20if%20you%20get%20offered%20the%20job%20or%20the%20opportunity%20at%20the%20conclusion%20of%20the%20meeting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20don't%20worry%20if%20you%20haven't%20received%20an%20offer%20on%20the%20spot.%20I've%20once%20offered%20someone%20a%20part%20time%20PA%20role%20immediately.%20However%2C%20it%20didn't%20work%20out%20long%20term%20because%20I'd%20allowed%20my%20emotions%20in%20the%20interview%20to%20take%20over%20from%20an%20objective%20view%20of%20the%20candidate's%20work%20record.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c629ebc5-beae-4c6b-8b1e-9c315dd04752%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EPositive%20body%20language%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20subtle%20sign%20that%20an%20interview%20went%20well%20is%20the%20interviewers'%20body%20language%20and%20how%20they%20relate%20to%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20general%20tone%20and%20demeanor%20of%20your%20interviewers%20at%20the%20conclusion%20of%20the%20interview%20can%20sometimes%20give%20you%20clues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20a%20successful%20interview%20in%20my%20career%2C%20I%20noticed%20the%20panel%20smiled%20and%20laughed%20collaboratively.%20They%20exchanged%20compliments%20openly%20and%20asked%20me%20questions%20about%20non-job-related%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGood%20body%20language%20includes%20smiling%2C%20laughing%2C%20making%20jokes%2C%20and%20being%20engaged%20and%20curious%20about%20what%20you're%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBody%20language%20isn't%20a%20definitive%20sign%2C%20however.%20People%20can%20be%20good%20actors.%20Don't%20read%20everything%20into%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220c67631c-ab5e-4a82-84e9-f9d218b4ef58%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHaving%20a%20good%20rapport%20with%20the%20interviewer%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20a%20good%20rapport%20with%20the%20interviewer%20does%20suggest%20that%20things%20have%20gone%20well.%20When%20I%20give%20interviews%2C%20I%20usually%20ask%20a%20fun%20first%20question%20to%20lighten%20the%20mood%20like%20%26quot%3BWhich%20foot