%20industry%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c82398ce-a87e-4509-bfef-0d3875be1de6%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20SB%201047%20would%20change%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bill's%20authors%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsd11.senate.ca.gov%2Fnews%2Fsenator-wieners-groundbreaking-artificial-intelligence-bill-advances-assembly-floor-amendments%23%3A~%3Atext%3DSB%25201047%2520is%2520legislation%2520to%2Cand%2520most%2520powerful%2520AI%2520systems.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esay%C2%A0its%20goal%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20to%20%26quot%3Bensure%20the%20safe%20development%20of%20large-scale%20artificial%20intelligence%20systems%20by%20establishing%20clear%2C%20predictable%2C%20common-sense%20safety%20standards%20for%20developers%20of%20the%20largest%20and%20most%20powerful%20AI%20systems.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20would%20apply%20to%20companies%20developing%20models%20that%20cost%20over%20%24100%20million%20to%20train%20or%20use%20high%20levels%20of%20computing%20power.%20These%20companies%20would%20be%20required%20to%20safety%20test%20new%20technologies%20before%20making%20them%20publicly%20available.%20They%20would%20also%20have%20to%20build%20%26quot%3Bfull%20shutdown%26quot%3B%20capabilities%20into%20their%20models%20and%20be%20held%20liable%20for%20all%20technology%20applications.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bill%20also%20establishes%20legal%20standards%20for%20AI%20developers%20%E2%80%94%20outlining%20%26quot%3Bunlawful%20acts%26quot%3B%20for%20which%20California's%20attorney%20general%20could%20sue%20companies%2C%20setting%20protections%20for%20whistleblowers%2C%20and%20creating%20a%20board%20to%20set%20compute%20limits%20on%20AI%20models%20and%20issue%20regulatory%20guidance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22590224af-e40d-4c75-8557-2bcb9de258c3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Big%20Tech%20thinks%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20developers%20the%20bill%20will%20most%20likely%20impact%20haven't%20been%20welcoming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20like%20Meta%2C%20OpenAI%2C%20and%20Anthropic%20%E2%80%94%20which%20are%20funneling%20millions%20into%20building%20and%20training%20large%20language%20models%20%E2%80%94%20have%20lobbied%20state%20legislators%20for%20changes.%20Meta%20said%20the%20initial%20legislation%20would%20hamper%20innovation%20and%20make%20it%20less%20likely%20that%20companies%20would%20allow%20their%20model%20to%20be%20open%20source.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20bill%20also%20actively%20discourages%20the%20release%20of%20open-source%20AI%20because%20providers%20would%20have%20no%20way%20to%20open-source%20models%20without%20facing%20untenable%20legal%20liability%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.politico.com%2Fe0%2Ffd%2Fe56dfaad40b39f29dd1dfa1164da%2Fsb-1047-letter-6-25-24.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMeta%20wrote%20in%20a%20letter%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20Wiener%20in%20June.%20That's%20likely%20to%20have%20ramifications%20on%20the%20small%20business%20ecosystem%20by%20lessening%20the%20likelihood%20of%20them%20using%20%26quot%3Bfree%2C%20readily%20available%20and%20fine-tuned%20models%20to%20create%20new%20jobs%2C%20businesses%2C%20tools%2C%20and%20services%20that%20often%20go%20on%20to%20be%20used%20by%20other%20businesses%2C%20governments%2C%20and%20civil%20society%20groups.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fheres-ai-company-amazon-betting-billions-on-anthropic-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAnthropic%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20has%20positioned%20itself%20as%20a%20safety-conscious%20AI%20company%2C%20wasn't%20happy%20with%20early%20versions%20of%20the%20bill%20and%20lobbied%20lawmakers%20for%20changes.%20It%20calls%20for%20a%20greater%20focus%20on%20deterring%20companies%20from%20building%20unsafe%20models%20rather%20than%20enforcing%20stringent%20laws%20before%20catastrophic%20incidents%20happen.%20It%20also%20suggests%20that%20companies%20that%20meet%20the%20%24100%20million%20threshold%20should%20be%20able%20to%20set%20their%20own%20standards%20for%20safety%20testing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bill%20has%20also%20drawn%20criticism%20from%20venture%20capitalists%2C%20executives%2C%20and%20other%20tech%20industry%20members.%20Anjney%20Midha%2C%20a%20general%20partner%20at%20Andreessen%20Horowitz%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fa16z.com%2Fsb-1047-what-you-need-to-know-with-anjney-midha%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecalled%20it%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3Bone%20of%20the%20most%20anti-competitive%20proposals%20I've%20seen%20in%20a%20long%20time.%26quot%3B%20He%20believes%20legislators%20should%20focus%20on%20%26quot%3Bregulating%20specific%20high-risk%20applications%20and%20malicious%20end%20users.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECalifornia%20legislators%20made%20a%20handful%20of%20the%20suggested%20changes%20%E2%80%94%20all%20of%20which%20made%20it%20into%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fleginfo.legislature.ca.gov%2Ffaces%2FbillNavClient.xhtml%3Fbill_id%3D202320240SB1047%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20latest%20version%20of%20the%20bill%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20updated%20version%20now%20prevents%20the%20California%20Attorney%20General's%20Office%20from%20suing%20AI%20developers%20before%20a%20catastrophic%20event%20happens.%20And%20while%20the%20bill%20initially%20called%20for%20a%20new%20government%20agency%20to%20oversee%20the%20enforcement%20of%20new%20laws%2C%20it%20has%20since%20pared%20that%20down%20to%20a%20board%20within%20the%20state's%20Government%20Operations%20Agency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20Anthropic%20told%20BI%20that%20it's%20%26quot%3Breviewing%20the%20new%20bill%20language%20as%20it%20becomes%20available.%26quot%3B%20Meta%20and%20OpenAI%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESmaller%20founders%20are%20apprehensive%20but%20also%20a%20bit%20more%20optimistic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EArun%20Subramaniyam%2C%20the%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20enterprise-focused%20generative%20AI%20company%20Articul8%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20no%20one%20understands%20the%20new%20board's%20%26quot%3Bsweeping%20powers%26quot%3B%20or%20how%20its%20directors%20will%20be%20appointed.%20He%20also%20believes%20the%20bill%20will%20impact%20companies%20beyond%20the%20Big%20Tech%20players%20since%20even%20well-funded%20startups%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Emight%20meet%20the%20%24100%20million%20training%20threshold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20he%20said%20he%20supports%20the%20bill's%20establishment%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eof%20a%20public%20cloud%20computing%20cluster%2C%20CalCompute%2C%20dedicated%20to%20researching%20the%20safe%20deployment%20of%20large-scale%20AI%20models.%20This%20cluster%20could%20bring%20more%20equity%20to%20researchers%20and%20groups%20that%20don't%20have%20the%20funds%20to%20evaluate%20AI%20models%20on%20their%20own.%20He%20also%20believes%20the%20reporting%20requirements%20on%20developers%20will%20increase%20transparency%2C%20benefiting%20Articul8's%20work%20in%20the%20long%20run.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20the%20industry's%20future%20hinges%20on%20how%20general-purpose%20models%20are%20regulated.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20good%20that%20the%20state%20is%20looking%20at%20regulating%20this%20early%2C%20but%20the%20vocabulary%20needs%20to%20be%20a%20little%20more%20balanced%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornia-ai-bill-makes-openai-meta-google-anthropic-nervous-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1724059801000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66c22a4db4912df3ae1c8208%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornia-ai-bill-makes-openai-meta-google-anthropic-nervous-2024-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22California%20wants%20to%20hold%20onto%20its%20lead%20in%20the%20AI%20arms%20race%20and%20regulate%20it%20at%20the%20same%20time.%20A%20propose