d%20residence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EExperience%20with%20electricity%20bills%20before%20going%20solar%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSince%20we%20are%20a%20large%20family%20living%20in%20a%20big%20house%2C%20we%20have%20a%20power%20connection%20supplying%20around%2025%20to%2030%20kW%20of%20electricity%20at%20home.%20Our%20electricity%20bill%20would%20vary%20season%20to%20season%2C%20but%20in%20the%20summer%2C%20it%20would%20come%20up%20to%20around%20Rs%2050%2C000%20to%20Rs%2060%2C000%20in%20June%20and%20July%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAnd%20during%20the%20winter%20season%2C%20our%20two-month%20electricity%20bill%20would%20drop%20to%20approximately%20Rs%2010%2C000%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%20Except%20for%20four%20cities%2C%20Haryana%20follows%20a%20system%20of%20clubbing%20bills%20of%20two%20months.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20decided%20to%20go%20solar%20about%20four%20years%20back%20and%20initially%20installed%20a%2010%20kW%20rooftop%20solar%20system%20to%20try%20it%20out.%20Haryana%20has%20implemented%20a%20net%20metering%20system%2C%20which%20means%20that%20whatever%20electricity%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20use%20%5Bgenerated%20by%20my%20solar%20system%5D%2C%20I%20sell%20it%20back%20to%20the%20grid%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20explains.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20final%20electricity%20bill%20I%20pay%20is%20the%20net%20difference%20between%20the%20power%20I%20consume%20%5Bfrom%20conventional%20sources%2C%20not%20solar%5D%20and%20the%20power%20I%20sell%20back%20to%20the%20grid.%20So%20that%E2%80%99s%20where%20we%20started%20with%20a%2010%20kW%20solar%20connection%20initially%20and%20then%20we%20saw%20a%20great%20benefit%20here%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2FSandeep-Mall-